The paper deals with morphing planar graph drawings, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of contractions and the preservation of planarity suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of unidirectional morphing steps involves the movement of vertices along lines with the same direction, which could be related to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the simplification of a previous proof, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
